##3 / 16 doing one thing is actually a "dry run" for another

Wechat Ballon Park

Features, night face wall

16 March, London.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At ten o'clock, through the window came the clattering laughter of the children in the kindergarten. Blue Sky White clouds, the sun dazzling, "the children have not come home ah" ... this is the reaction of the heart.

Boris Johnson held another press conference today, "today we need to go further" , to encourage work from home, to stop socializing, to stop going to the theatre, going to concerts and drinking in pubs. Maqueron announced the closure of the French border, and my party loving landlord decided today to stay in France, at the Fontainbleau House for a while. Well, if she were driving back today, I'd be worried she'd be knocking about London, at Fontainau, riding around the woods.

Go further today: Roommate made me a Shokugeki no Soma of Apple Risotto with Fried Bacon and a garland bean curd soup. One Minute it's a French restaurant, the next it's spring in China.

Walking along the riverfront trail of Battersea Park two days ago, I suddenly saw a weeping willow on the riverbank at the bridge head. The branches had already sprouted, the trunk of the tree was leaning over the river, i finally saw it, as if it were a bench with a vermilion back. I should have been here for her.

Homesick? Yes. If at home at this time, and mom and dad into the mountains, dig and Shepherd's purse, Hickory is about to open. Though the fruit trees in the orchard are mostly Cash crop, stout and stunted, the peach blossoms are Gaudy to behold, but at the foot of the hill, from a distance, the peach blossoms were speckled pink on the slowly turning Green Mountains, rolling hills next to the river during the dry season, but the earth slope has a continuous pink.

And so, for a moment it felt like a holiday, as if you weren't hiding from illness, as if you were, an empty calendar, an hour on the phone with a friend, not as if you were going to die, as if you were actually working, the money to be earned, the livelihood to be earned, the manuscript to be handed in, the rent to be paid, will wander back after this illusion disappears. But in the case of an epidemic, life just stops. Some stubborn prejudices in the brain are even shaken. The self-consistency system suddenly breaks down, and you suddenly feel the need to examine yourself and talk to others.

Song Ta called, and he's the guy who, once upon a time, thought he had nothing to say, and suddenly felt he needed to talk to someone. I told him that it was the turn of Spring and summer for me, that I woke up and felt that the abstract questions were becoming concrete. He felt that this was much more powerful than that. An incident in a certain region spread to the whole world and became a common subject of mankind, and even changed the global political and economic structure. The last time this was done, or a chain reaction between 9 / 11 and terrorism. China is now beginning to intervene in the global fight against the epidemic this chain reaction, "one province, one country" is also a good diplomatic and show strength of the opportunity. Doing one thing is actually a "dry run" for another.

Wear a long raincoat and N99 mask to the park in the evening. I passed the supermarket and found the vegetables on the shelves. There were fewer people in the park than usual, but no one wore a mask, let alone one as high-profile as mine. We're a retirement community on the west side of London, mostly white. Of course passers-by will find me armed, and look at me, and I'll smile with my eyes, until they stop laughing, and I'll talk to them, ask them why they're taking it so easy because the information they're receiving so far is so unimportant, and then tell them how to defend themselves afterwards. One Grandmother said she'd think about wearing big sunglasses later; a table of young men at the Bar said, how could we be afraid of viruses? We're all so young, as if to tell them solemnly that it's pneumonia, one of the British girls suddenly began speaking halting Chinese. She had studied Chinese for a year, spent three months in Beijing, and decided to give it up. "It's too hard, " said one very chic-dressed sister, go out and walk the dog and go about her life, and lock down completely, because she doesn't have a mask. We watched the flowers together for a while through her black shell. The Cherry blossoms are in full bloom, a full week earlier than last year, and there is no snow this year.

I came out here today as a test to see what it would be like to dress up like this. But this strategy of mine, knowing that I'm going to be noticed, so the way I interact and be funny, isn't something that everyone does. Over the years in London, I've been pelted with stones by children, walking on the road occasionally hear "ni-hao-ma" "mei-nv" , more than a month ago to wear a mask will be walked around, two days ago in the street men make a gesture to remove my mask, I feel like most of the time the obvious "discrimination" , is the discrimination itself want to tease, bully, disgusting, they know this is wrong, the act itself is a temporary release. I'm not afraid of that, because people who know what they're doing are guilty. On the contrary, what should be more vigilant is those who are just, bright, lasting bully.
